Cheerleaders are funny. 
They'll do anything to win The Nationals and in the dark comedic world of Paul Thomas, that includes "busting up" the competition. 
But that takes thugs... and thugs cost money. 
What's a cheerleader to do? Have a car wash! A bake sale! An amateur photo contest! And if that doesn't work, clean their clocks in poker! Car Wash. 
It's all about sex, envy, charity and greed.
